<title>CHINA: HK GDP rises 6.1 pct in 1st quarter of 1997.</title>
<headline>HK GDP rises 6.1 pct in 1st quarter of 1997.</headline>
<dateline>HONG KONG 1997-08-04</dateline>
<text>
<p>The Census and Statistics Department gave the following estimates of real gross domestic product (GDP) growth (in percent).</p>
<p>				 1st qtr '97  4th qtr '96 (unrevised)</p>
<p> GDP			     6.1	    5.5</p>
<p>Components</p>
<p>Private consumption</p>
<p> expenditure:		  5.0	    6.4</p>
<p>Government consumption</p>
<p> expenditure:		  4.4	    5.2</p>
<p>				 1st qtr '97  4th qtr '96 (unrevised)</p>
<p>Gross domestic fixed</p>
<p> capital formation:	 18.7	   20.9</p>
<p> Domestic exports:	  -3.6	   -7.2</p>
<p> Re-exports:		   5.5	    8.0</p>
<p> Exports of services:	5.8	    5.6</p>
<p>Implicit price</p>
<p> deflator of GDP:	    6.6	    6.2</p>
<p>Estimates of individual expenditure components of GDP for the 1st quarter of 1997 were updated based on the latest data available from various sources, the government said.  </p>
<p>** (for 4th quarter only) ** For 1996 as a whole, GDP rose 4.9 percent, the government said.</p>
<p>The following table is of revised GDP data. All figures are year-on-year at constant (1990) market prices.</p>
<p>				 1996 Q4   1996 Q3   1996 Q2   1996 Q1</p>
<p> GDP			     5.7	 5.2	 4.6	 4.0</p>
<p>Components</p>
<p>Private consumption</p>
<p> expenditure:		  6.7	 4.8	 3.5	 3.9</p>
<p>Government consumption</p>
<p> expenditure:		  4.9	 4.7	 5.1	 2.8</p>
<p>				 1996 Q4   1996 Q3   1996 Q2   1996 Q1</p>
<p>Gross domestic fixed</p>
<p> capital formation:	  21.3	 6.0	10.2     11.3</p>
<p> Total exports of goods    5.4	 4.9	 3.9	4.9</p>
<p> Imports of goods	    6.5	 3.4	 2.2	5.2</p>
<p> Exports of services	 5.3	 6.3	 4.9	7.2</p>
<p> Imports of services	 2.7	 1.6	 1.4	2.1</p>
<p>-- Hong Kong Newsroom (852) 2843 6441</p>
